#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.7:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Sekhabalavagga"
msgstr "1. Powers of a Trainee"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: kāmesupalāḷitasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Kāmasutta"
msgstr "7. Sensual Pleasures"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: sattā kāmesu laḷitā → palāḷitā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.7:1.1"
msgid "“Yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, sattā kāmesu laḷitā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, sentient beings are mostly charmed by sensual pleasures."

#. VAR: Asitabyābhaṅgiṃ → asitabyābhaṅgi cepi (?)
msgctxt "an5.7:1.2"
msgid ""
"Asitabyābhaṅgiṃ, bhikkhave, kulaputto ohāya agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito "
"hoti, ‘saddhāpabbajito kulaputto’ti alaṃvacanāya."
msgstr ""
"When someone from a good family has abandoned the scythe and flail and gone "
"forth from the lay life to homelessness, they’re qualified to be called ‘a "
"faithful renunciate from a good family’."

msgctxt "an5.7:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. VAR: Labbhā → labbhā hi (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.7:1.4"
msgid "Labbhā, bhikkhave, yobbanena kāmā te ca kho yādisā vā tādisā vā."
msgstr "Because a youth can get sensual pleasures of this kind or that."

msgctxt "an5.7:1.5"
msgid ""
"Ye ca, bhikkhave, hīnā kāmā ye ca majjhimā kāmā ye ca paṇītā kāmā, sabbe "
"kāmā ‘kāmā’tveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"Now, all sensual pleasures are just reckoned as ‘sensual pleasures’, "
"regardless of whether they’re inferior, average, or superior."

#. VAR: kaṭhalaṃ → kathalaṃ (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an5.7:1.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako dhātiyā "
"pamādamanvāya kaṭṭhaṃ vā kaṭhalaṃ vā mukhe āhareyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a little baby boy who, because of his nurse’s negligence, "
"puts a stick or stone in his mouth."

#. VAR: sīghaṃ sīghaṃ → sīghasīghaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.7:1.7"
msgid "Tamenaṃ dhāti sīghaṃ sīghaṃ manasi kareyya;"
msgstr "The nurse would very quickly notice"

msgctxt "an5.7:1.8"
msgid "sīghaṃ sīghaṃ manasi karitvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ āhareyya."
msgstr "and try to take it out."

msgctxt "an5.7:1.9"
msgid ""
"No ce sakkuṇeyya sīghaṃ sīghaṃ āharituṃ, vāmena hatthena sīsaṃ pariggahetvā "
"dakkhiṇena hatthena vaṅkaṅguliṃ karitvā salohitampi āhareyya."
msgstr ""
"If that didn’t work, she’d cradle his head with her left hand, and take it "
"out using a hooked finger of her right hand, even if it drew blood."

msgctxt "an5.7:1.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an5.7:1.11"
msgid "‘Atthesā, bhikkhave, kumārassa vihesā;"
msgstr "I admit she’d know, ‘This will distress the child,"

msgctxt "an5.7:1.12"
msgid "nesā natthī’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "there’s no denying.’"

#. VAR: etaṃ → evaṃ (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.7:1.13"
msgid ""
"Karaṇīyañca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, dhātiyā atthakāmāya hitesiniyā "
"anukampikāya, anukampaṃ upādāya."
msgstr ""
"Still, it should be done by a nurse who wants what’s best for him, out of "
"kindness and compassion."

#. VAR: anapekkhā dāni → anapekkhā pana (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.7:1.14"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, so kumāro vuddho hoti alaṃpañño, anapekkhā dāni, "
"bhikkhave, dhāti tasmiṃ kumāre hoti:"
msgstr ""
"And when the boy has grown up and has enough sense, his nurse would not "
"worry about him, thinking:"

msgctxt "an5.7:1.15"
msgid "‘attagutto dāni kumāro nālaṃ pamādāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘The boy can look after himself. He won’t be negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.7:2.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yāvakīvañca bhikkhuno saddhāya akataṃ hoti kusalesu "
"dhammesu, hiriyā akataṃ hoti kusalesu dhammesu, ottappena akataṃ hoti "
"kusalesu dhammesu, vīriyena akataṃ hoti kusalesu dhammesu, paññāya akataṃ "
"hoti kusalesu dhammesu, anurakkhitabbo tāva me so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hoti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I still need to look after a mendicant who hasn’t finished "
"developing faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom regarding "
"skillful qualities."

#. VAR: dānāhaṃ → panāhaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.7:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno saddhāya kataṃ hoti kusalesu dhammesu, "
"hiriyā kataṃ hoti kusalesu dhammesu, ottappena kataṃ hoti kusalesu dhammesu, "
"vīriyena kataṃ hoti kusalesu dhammesu, paññāya kataṃ hoti kusalesu dhammesu, "
"anapekkho dānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tasmiṃ bhikkhusmiṃ homi:"
msgstr ""
"But when a mendicant has finished developing faith, conscience, prudence, "
"energy, and wisdom regarding skillful qualities, I think:"

msgctxt "an5.7:2.3"
msgid "‘attagutto dāni bhikkhu nālaṃ pamādāyā’”ti."
msgstr "‘They can look after themselves. They won’t be negligent.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.7:2.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
